cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CY

This paper deals with network security and data transmission, which are relevant to several sub-categories. However, the focus on data forensics and botnet removal suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category. The use of domain generation algorithms and dynamic DNS services also suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper may also be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) due to the potential ethical implications of covert data transport protocols.
